<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ruminate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ruminate,</orth> 1) intr. to muse, to meditate, to ponder: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.321" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 321</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.252" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 252</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 132</bibl>. With <cit><quote>on:</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 180</bibl></cit>. With a subordinate clause: <bibl n="shak. son 64.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 64, 11</bibl>.<lb />2) tr. to muse on, to meditate over and over again: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.274" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 274</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.101" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 5, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 141</bibl>.
